"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-team-gb-paris-olympics-medal-target-b1151951.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  Britain has been predicted to exceed its medal tally from the lastOlympics in Paristhis summer.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 245, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.93570649874922, \"rank\": 0.06871108932123662, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GBathletes came away from the Covid-delayed Tokyo Games three years ago with 64 medals in all.\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Gracenote Virtual Medal Table, a statistical model based on past Olympics, World Championships and World Cups to predict results, has estimated the British contingent will come away with an improvement of 66 medals in all from the French capital.\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 599, \"end\": 606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9814417012070549, \"rank\": 0.017872327938874492, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 682, \"end\": 688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5655059042927918, \"rank\": 0.5482743195217267, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the gold count is set for a big drop to just 13, a noticeable fall from the 22 golds won in Japan in 2021.\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 795, \"end\": 800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9857051590815418, \"rank\": 0.01249801184772585, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 100 days to go from Paris, the British team is far from being finalised for the summer Games but the 66 medals are expected to come from 22 sports in all, with Britain tipped for the third-highest medal tally of all the nations.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 1042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 834, \"end\": 839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999988117452, \"rank\": 1.188118204574617e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 845, \"end\": 852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9814417012070549, \"rank\": 0.017872327938874492, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 974, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.93570649874922, \"rank\": 0.06871108932123662, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it is anticipated the Brits will finish fourth in the medal table behind the United States, China and France, by virtue of the Olympic hosts' highergold medalcount.\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1124, \"end\": 1137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.7709790198352912, \"rank\": 0.24206672595687292, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1139, \"end\": 1144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_mainland_China\", \"score\": 0.9021542840298304, \"rank\": 0.06862262493155982, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_mainland_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_mainland_China\"}, {\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.980720335797154, \"rank\": 0.018510420624275766, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The British cycling team are once again expected to be responsible for the highest medal haul of 12 medals across track cycling, BMX and mountain biking but none on the road.Beth Shrieveris favoured to successfully defend her BMX racing gold from the last Games, withTom Pidcockexpected to drop back a spot after his golden run in the mountain biking in 2021.\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1217, \"end\": 1232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}, {\"begin\": 1342, \"end\": 1345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9986171168942816, \"rank\": 0.001384159201283284, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1439, \"end\": 1449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997071954996, \"rank\": 2.9280469748077296e-07, \"text\": \"BMX racing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the wake ofLaura Kenny's retirement, Katie Archibald looks to be the star turn of the British track cycling contingent with the Scot going for gold in three endurance events: the team pursuit, where Britain are ranked No1, the omnium and the madison.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1614, \"end\": 1629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Archibald\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\"}, {\"begin\": 1663, \"end\": 1670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9814417012070549, \"rank\": 0.017872327938874492, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1776, \"end\": 1783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.93570649874922, \"rank\": 0.06871108932123662, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won all three at the most recent Olympic qualifying event in Canada.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1893, \"end\": 1899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9183504902378282, \"rank\": 0.08564476441620994, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a tough Tokyo Olympics without a single gold medal, British rowers are expected to return to top of the medal table with four gold medals in total and a particularly strong contingent in the men's sweep: pair, four and eight.\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 2133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1960, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9814417012070549, \"rank\": 0.017872327938874492, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the swimmers are not being backed to echo their medal heroics in Tokyo which entailed four gold medals, with no golds predicted for a team spearheaded by the likes ofAdam Peaty, bidding for a third straight Olympic gold, and all-rounder Duncan Scott, who has yet to pick up an individual Olympic gold.\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2204, \"end\": 2209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9928388448037263, \"rank\": 0.007212620435533466, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And no golds are anticipated in the athletics although lesser medals are expected from the likes ofJosh Kerr, Keely Hodgkinson and Dina Asher-Smith.\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2552, \"end\": 2568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 2573, \"end\": 2589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dina Asher-Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday